<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; parameters must be passed as base types. Despite the declared types, most</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; of the functions provided operate only on branches of the type hierarchy.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; The declared parameter names are descriptive and specify which type is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; required. Additionally, each type hierarchy is documented along with the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; functions that operate upon it. For more detail, refer to LLVM&#39;s C++ code.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><Highlight kind="comment"> &#42; If in doubt, refer to Core.cpp, which performs parameter downcasts in the</Highlight></CodeLine>
